Hi,

in my application, I'm using jquery-tokeninput to select some values containing parantheses.
The highlighting Regexp take these parantheses from the value into account while counting the regexp references.

That is leading to two problems:
1. The matching element is not highlighted, if the value contains parantheses.
2. If the value contains only a "(" and no ")", the regexp will fail and no selection list is shown at all.

I solved it with the following `onResult` callback, but I think, it should be the default:

``` javascript
    onResult: function (results) {
      jQuery.each(results, function (index, value) {
        value.name = value.name.replace(/\(/g, '&#40;').replace(/\)/g, '&#41;');
      });
      return results;
    }
```

